obo:ECO_0007695  a  owl:Class .

obo:ECO_0007719  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_265  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Experiment explanation: The authors systematically characterized the molecular and morphological nature of the docked and primed SV states with nanometer accuracy by the used of high-pressure freezing (HPF), freeze substitution (FS), and electron tomography (ET) of mouse mutants synapses. Taking in account as analysis parameters: SV Diameter and Number of SVs within a distance of: 100, 40, 0-5, 0-2nm of AZ.\n\nProtein Function: The analysis of Syb- 2 KO terminals revealed a severe reduction in the number of docked SVs and a prominent accumulation of SVs close (4-8 nm) to the AZ (Figure 4).However, Syb-2 KO synapses showed no changes in the number of SVs within 40 or 100 nm of the AZ. Based on these results, the authors concluded that Syb-2 is required for SV Docking.\n\nProtein Location: Confocal microscopy of WT slices showed a specific punctate labeling of Syb-2, which highly colocalized with VGLUT1 but was absent in Syb-2 KO cultures (data not shown).. Experimental description: The authors employed hippocampal organotypic slice cultures from mice lacking Synaptobrevin-2 and also, other key presynaptic proteins, cryofixation, and three-dimensional electron tomography to study the mechanism of synaptic vesicle docking in the same experimental setting, with high precision, and in a near-native state." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_265" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

